The given implementation is iterative, not recursive. To demonstrate this misconception, I need to rewrite the solution as a recursive function where the student unnecessarily includes an else clause.

The student would convert the iterative solution to a recursive one and add an unnecessary else clause because they believe that's required for recursion.

